Partly referring to the fact that, being a nomadic people‚ they never stayed beyond a year in one spot, partly to the practice of relieving (recreat) those who had done the work one year (defunctos labori- bus) by substitutes (vicarii) who had meanwhile acted as combatants but who now had to take their fair turn (sors aequalis) of work.
